OL,3,COne in five Britons would end
OL,4,Crelationship over difference in salary
OL,5,C` survey
OL,7,FHowever, more than one in six Britons
OL,8,F(17%) say they feel uncomfortable
OL,9,Ftalking about money, with 19% saying
OL,10,Fthey have experienced clashing
OL,11,Fattitudes towards spending and saving
OL,12,Fand 18% have felt the pressure of a
OL,13,Fpartner relying on them financially.
OL,15,FHalf of people (50%) believe that
OL,16,Fmoney is too private to discuss, and
OL,17,F23% avoid such conversations out of
OL,18,Ffear of judgment and criticism.
