OL,3,COne in five Britons would end
OL,4,Crelationship over difference in salary
OL,5,C` survey
OL,7,F"Money conversations can be
OL,8,Femotionally loaded, making it
OL,9,Fdifficult to openly talk about
OL,10,Ffinances. People fear judgment,
OL,11,Fcriticism or conflict ` especially if
OL,12,Fthey carry feelings of anxiety, not
OL,13,Fbeing 'enough', or concerns of being
OL,14,Fperceived as privileged, burdensome or
OL,15,Firresponsible.
OL,17,F"Taking a practical and proactive
OL,18,Fapproach can make money conversations
OL,19,Ffeel less personal and more
OL,20,Fmanageable, rather than being
OL,21,Femotionally taxing."
